  "name": "John 18:28–40",
  "localizedName": "John 18:28–40",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The Jewish leaders moved Jesus to the palace of the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108047",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Roman"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " governor Pilate."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The Roman government didn’t want any Jew to claim that he was Israel’s true king. Jewish messiahs who claimed to be king would lead armed groups to attack the government. The Romans would put them to death on a cross. So the Jewish leaders charged Jesus with claiming to be a king."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Pilate and Jesus talked about being king, about power and about truth. Pilate couldn’t understand what Jesus was talking about. Jesus is indeed the King. He is King of Israel and of the world. But his kingdom isn’t like human governments. Jesus’ kingdom is God’s kingdom and it’s based on truth and on love."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus was showing God’s love as he was on trial. He was giving up his life to set others free. The crowd asked Pilate to set "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108076",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Barabbas"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " free from prison instead of Jesus."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
